<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="30" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,285]" pageId="7" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,151,176]" pageId="7" pageNumber="30">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new species seems closely related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Flint 1991" authorityName="Flint" authorityYear="1991" box="[804,1053,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Metrichia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malada">
<emphasis box="[804,927,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="30">M. malada</emphasis>
Flint 1991
</taxonomicName>
based on the overall similarity in shape and structure of inferior appendages and phallic apparatus. However, 
<taxonomicName authority="Mey &amp; Ospina-Torres, 2018" authorityName="Mey &amp; Ospina-Torres" authorityYear="2018" box="[1060,1212,189,212]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Metrichia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trisignata" status="spec. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1060,1212,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="30">M. trisignata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1224,1344,188,212]" pageId="7" pageNumber="30">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1224,1344,188,212]" pageId="7" pageNumber="30" rank="species">spec. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be distinguished from that species by the more quadrate shape of the inferior appendages each bearing three small teeth or dark points on the apical margin, and by the simple apices of the dorsolateral hooks.
</paragraph>
